@Node introduction "Introduction"
        @{B}Introduction@{UB}

  Giamby Scroll is a simply program that permit you to make easy videoscrolling from a IFF ILBM image file. This picture can be bigger than screen dimensions and can have 256 cols. maximum.
  When you select the image, GiambyScroll puts on his interface some information on the picture (e. g. Width, Eight and Colors) and, if you select "Scroll" button, it will open a custom screen where is the image file.
  @{B}WARNING:@{UB} At this time you must push "S" (@{B}S@{UB}tart/@{B}S@{UB}top) key to begin or Stop the Scrolling else you may press "X" key to e@{B}X@{UB}it.
  For other commands see @{"Scrolling commands" link inscroll}

        @{B}WARRANTY@{UB}

  GIAMBY SCROLL SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS-IS" AND SUBJECT TO CHANGE; NO WARRANTIES ARE MADE.  ALL USE IS AT YOUR OWN RISK.  NO LIABILITY OR RESPONSIBILITY IS ASSUMED.

@EndNode introduction


@Node install "Install"
        @{B}How install Giamby Scroll@{UB}

  To install Giamby Scroll you may copy the Giamby Scroll drawer when you want that it be placed.
  Remeber: Giamby Scroll needs of iffparse.library and locale.library (only if you want localization).

@EndNode install


@Node gads
        @{B}Gadgets@{UB}

  - @{B}Picture@{UB}: Show picture selected name;
  - @{B}O@{UB}: Open an ASL file requester;
  - @{B}Page Size@{UB}: Show @{B}Width@{UB} and @{B}Height@{UB} of the Page;
  - @{B}Screen Info@{UB}: Show some information on the selected image screen (@{B}Width, Height, Colors@{UB});
  - @{B}Delay@{UB}: Permit to select in scrolling delay;
  - @{B}Scroll@{UB}: Begin the process of scrolling, see also @{"Scrolling commands" link inscroll};
  - @{B}Standart Speed@{UB}: Select a standart delay for the scrolling;

@EndNode gads


@Node menu "Menu Items"
        @{B}Menu Items@{UB}

  @{I}Project@{UI}:
   - @{B}About@{UB}: Show some information about the program and about the @{"Author" link me};
   - @{B}Quit@{UB}: Exit from the program:
  @{I}Settings@{UI}:
   - @{B}Select font...@{UB}: Open an ASL font requester quen you can select the default Giamby Scroll interface font;
   - @{B}Screen position@{UB}: Open a window when you can set the screen position. @{B}Note:@{UB} if you set this coordinates to 0, 0 the best screen position will be calculate automatically.

@EndNode menu


@Node inscroll
        @{B}Scrolling Commands{UB}

  - "@{B}S@{UB}": To Start or Stop the Scrolling;
  - "@{B}I@{UB}": To Init the image at the begin position;
  - "@{B}X@{UB}": To eXit from the scrolling process;
  - @{B}Up Arrow@{UB}: Move up the image;
  - @{B}Down Arrow@{UB}: Move down the image;
  - @{B}Left Arrow@{UB}: Move left the image;
  - @{B}Right Arrow@{UB}: Move right the image.

@EndNode inscroll


